HEADWORD: Proteroglypha
<hw>Pro`te*rog"ly*pha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ before + <?/ to carve.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
suborder of serpents including those that have permanently erect grooved
poison fangs, with ordinary teeth behind them in the jaws. It includes
the cobras, the asps, and the sea snakes. Called also
<altname>Proteroglyphia</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proterogynous</ent>⟦br⟧
